  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "# 3D Surface Gallery\n\nA tour of mathematical surfaces rendered as interactive 3D plots. We use\nMaxima's symbolic engine to **analyse** each surface — computing gradients,\nHessians, and curvatures — before handing the expressions to `ax-plots`\nfor visualization. This is the symbolic-numeric bridge in action: the CAS\nderives exact formulas, and the plotting library samples them numerically.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "load(\"numerics\")$\nload(\"ax-plots\")$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 121,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Classic Surfaces\n\nThree well-known quadric and cubic surfaces that appear throughout\nmultivariable calculus.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Saddle surface: z = x^2 - y^2 */\nax_draw3d(\n  explicit(x^2 - y^2, x, -2, 2, y, -2, 2),\n  title=\"Saddle Surface\", colorscale=\"RdBu\"\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 122,
      "outputs": [
