    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Curvature Analysis [S+N]\n\nThe **mean curvature** of a surface $z = f(x,y)$ is\n\n$$H = \\frac{(1+f_y^2)\\,f_{xx} - 2\\,f_x\\,f_y\\,f_{xy} + (1+f_x^2)\\,f_{yy}}{2\\,(1+f_x^2+f_y^2)^{3/2}}$$\n\nMaxima can derive this expression symbolically for any $f$, and then we\ncan visualize it as a heatmap to see where the surface bends most.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Symbolic mean curvature for the saddle f = x^2 - y^2 */\nfx : diff(f(x,y), x)$\nfy : diff(f(x,y), y)$\nfxx : diff(f(x,y), x, 2)$\nfyy : diff(f(x,y), y, 2)$\nfxy : diff(f(x,y), x, 1, y, 1)$\n\nmean_curv : ratsimp(\n  ((1 + fy^2)*fxx - 2*fx*fy*fxy + (1 + fx^2)*fyy)\n  / (2*(1 + fx^2 + fy^2)^(3/2))\n);",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 133,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "data": {
            "text/latex": [
              "{{4\\,y^2-4\\,x^2}\\over{\\left(4\\,y^2+4\\,x^2+1\\right)^{{{3}\\over{2}}}}}"
            ]
          },
          "execution_count": 133,
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "execute_result"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Contour plot of the mean curvature over the domain */\nax_draw2d(\n  ax_contour(mean_curv, x, -2, 2, y, -2, 2),\n  colorscale=\"RdBu\", ncontours=20,\n  title=\"Mean Curvature of x^2 - y^2\"\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 134,
      "outputs": [
        {
